        <section>
            <h2><u>Fest</u>ivals</h2>
            <p>Marathwada is home to numerous festivals that highlight its rich culture. Some of the prominent festivals
                include:</p>
        </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Gudi Padwa:</strong> The Marathi New Year celebrated with joy and traditional rituals.</li>
            <p>Gudi Padwa, celebrated as the Marathi New Year, holds special significance in the Marathwada region. It
                usually falls in March or April and marks the arrival of spring. The festival is characterized by
                vibrant rituals, where families clean and decorate their homes, creating intricate rangoli designs at
                their entrances. A central element of the celebration is the Gudi itself—a decorated pole adorned with a
                colorful silk cloth, a garland of flowers, and a brass pot, symbolizing prosperity and good fortune.
                People perform traditional pujas and offer prayers, expressing gratitude for the harvest. The day is
                also marked by the preparation of delicious dishes like puran poli and shrikhand, enjoyed in the company
                of family and friends. Folk music and dance add to the festive spirit, bringing communities together in
                joyous celebration. Gudi Padwa not only marks a new beginning but also reinforces cultural ties and
                familial bonds, making it a cherished occasion in Marathwada.</p>
            <section>
