            <li><strong>Diwali:</strong> The festival of lights, filled with joy and festivities.</li>
            <p>Diwali in Marathwada is celebrated with traditional rituals, including the worship of Goddess Lakshmi.
                Homes are adorned with diyas and rangoli, while families gather to share sweets and enjoy fireworks.</p>
            <p>
                Diwali in Marathwada is a vibrant and joyous celebration that illuminates homes and hearts with
                festivity. The festival of lights, symbolizing the victory of light over darkness and good over evil,
                brings families together for elaborate preparations. In the days leading up to Diwali, homes are
                thoroughly cleaned and adorned with colorful rangoli designs and oil lamps (diyas), creating a warm and
                inviting atmosphere.</p>
            <p>On the night of Diwali, families perform puja to Goddess Lakshmi, seeking blessings for prosperity and
                happiness. Traditional sweets and snacks, such as chakli and karanji, are prepared and shared among
                relatives and friends. The night sky comes alive with fireworks, filling the air with excitement and
                cheer.</p>
            <p>In Marathwada, community gatherings often include singing and dancing, further enhancing the festive
                spirit. The celebration emphasizes familial bonds and cultural heritage, making Diwali a cherished
                occasion that fosters unity and joy among the people of the region</p>
