            <li><strong>Shiv Jayanti:</strong> Celebrating the birth of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj.</li>
            <p>Shiv Jayanti, celebrating the birth of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj, is a significant event in Marathwada,
                reflecting the region's rich Maratha heritage. The festival typically falls in February or March and is
                marked by grand processions, cultural programs, and various events that honor the legacy of Shivaji
                Maharaj.</p>
            <p>Communities come together to organize rallies, featuring traditional music, dance, and reenactments of
                historical events from Shivaji’s life. Statues and portraits of the king are adorned with flowers, and
                speeches recounting his valor and contributions to Maharashtra are delivered.</p>
            <p>Schools and cultural organizations often hold competitions, such as debates and dramas, highlighting
                Shivaji’s life and ideals. Traditional foods are prepared, and the atmosphere is filled with enthusiasm
                and pride. The celebrations not only commemorate Shivaji's legacy but also foster a sense of unity and
                cultural identity among the people of Marathwada, making Shiv Jayanti a cherished occasion in the region
            </p>
