        <section>
            <h2><u>Cuis</u>ine</h2>
            <p>Marathwada cuisine is diverse and flavorful, characterized by its use of local ingredients and spices.
                Signature dishes include:</p>
        </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Biryanis:</strong> The region is famous for its flavorful biryanis, especially mutton and
                chicken varieties, often prepared with aromatic spices.</li>
            <p>
                Biryani from Marathwada is a culinary delight, celebrated for its rich flavors and aromatic spices. This
                regional variation often features tender meat, such as mutton or chicken, marinated with a blend of
                spices including saffron, cardamom, and cloves. The meat is cooked to perfection and layered with
                fragrant basmati rice, which absorbs all the flavorful juices.</p>
            <p>Biryani in Marathwada is usually accompanied by side dishes like raita (yogurt sauce) and salan (spicy
                gravy), enhancing the overall dining experience. It is a popular dish for celebrations, weddings, and
                special occasions, reflecting the rich culinary heritage of the region. The depth of flavor and the
                festive spirit surrounding its preparation make Marathwada biryani a must-try for any food lover</p>

            <section>
                <img src="https://media-assets.swiggy.com/swiggy/image/upload/fl_lossy,f_auto,q_auto,w_366/agwwamnhrofy1ysn6nz0"
                    alt="" width="400px">
