            <li><strong>Puran Poli:</strong> A sweet flatbread stuffed with a mixture of jaggery and lentils, popular
                during festivals.</li>
            <p>
                Puran Poli is a beloved traditional sweet flatbread from Marathwada, celebrated for its delightful taste
                and cultural significance. Made primarily from wheat flour, the dough is rolled out thin and stuffed
                with a flavorful filling of cooked chana dal (split chickpeas) mixed with jaggery, and often flavored
                with cardamom and nutmeg.</p>
            <p>The preparation of puran poli is often a communal affair, with families coming together to make large
                batches for festive gatherings. Each bite offers a perfect blend of sweetness and warmth, making it a
                comforting and nostalgic dish for many.</p>
            <section>
                <img src="https://peekncooksa.blob.core.windows.net/index-recipe/puran-poli2.jpg" alt="" width="450px">
            </section>
            <p></p>

            <li><strong>Thalipeeth:</strong> A multi-grain flatbread mixed with spices and herbs, typically served with
                yogurt or chutney.</li>
            <p>
                Thalipeeth is a traditional multi-grain flatbread that originates from Maharashtra, and it holds a
                special place in the culinary culture of Marathwada. Made from a blend of various flours—such as jowar
                (sorghum), bajra (pearl millet), and whole wheat—this nutritious dish is often spiced with ingredients
                like green chilies, cumin seeds, and coriander, giving it a unique flavor.</p>
            <p>This dish is not only hearty and filling but also reflects the agricultural practices of the region,
                utilizing locally grown grains. Thalipeeth is a popular choice for breakfast or as a snack, showcasing
                the wholesome and vibrant culinary heritage of Marathwada. Its versatility and rich flavors make it a
                beloved staple in many households.</p>
