            <h2><u>Art</u> & <u>Craft</u></h2>
            <p>Marathwada is known for its traditional art forms, including:</p>
        </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Paithani Sarees:</strong> Handwoven sarees characterized by intricate designs and vibrant
                colors, often worn during special occasions.</li>
            <p>
                Paithani sarees are a hallmark of traditional Maharashtrian attire, particularly celebrated in the
                Marathwada region. Known for their exquisite craftsmanship, these sarees are made from fine silk and
                feature intricate designs, often depicting motifs inspired by nature, such as peacocks and flowers, as
                well as traditional patterns like paisleys.</p>
            <p>The hallmark of a Paithani is its vibrant colors and the characteristic border, which is usually woven
                with gold or silver thread, adding to its elegance. The sarees are typically handwoven using a special
                weaving technique, making each piece unique and a testament to the artisan's skill.</p>
            <p>Paithani sarees are often worn during festive occasions, weddings, and cultural events, symbolizing grace
                and tradition. The rich heritage associated with Paithani weaving not only reflects the artistic legacy
                of Marathwada but also plays a significant role in the region's cultural identity, making it a cherished
                garment for generations.</p>
